HEADWORD: Trisulcate
<hw>Tri*sul"cate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[Pref.
<ets>tri-</ets> + <ets>sulcate</ets>.]</ety> <def>Having three furrows,
forks, or prongs; having three grooves or sulci;
three-grooved.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

